Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: Great food but the place is better suited for take away rather than sit in. The atmosphere is very relaxed but not too many places to sit down.

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: Amazing place! Definitely a must go if if you like asian food. All the staff is so kind. Did I mention that is delicious? If you come, order the Nasi rames.

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: Really delicious Indonesian food. Nice ambiance, small and lovely restaurant. Good service. Frog legs, gado gado, and spekkoek are recommended.

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: Great food and has been in the same place for more than twenty years.

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: Babi pangang was not served as we expected but was tasty nevertheless. Excellent vegetarian selection

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: amazing food. scallops were cooked to perfection. fish was amazing. the next day went again. pea soup with stew was spicy sweet and was a delight. pork was great. you must book in advance. small restaurant, great ambience. service was attentive.

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: Vegetarian and vegan friendly. Get the vegetarian Nasi Rames. Food is good, but can be oily. Service can be chaotic at times and tables are not the cleanest.

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: The food was amazing, the service a little lacking. Not terrible, but took getting up to find the waitress to get another drink. Would highly recommend for the food though. Good sized portions and not too expensive. IMPORTANT-THEY ONLY TAKE CASH!

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: We ordered some vegetarian bami and nasi to go. Two customers came in after us and received their huge order of five dishes before we did our small one.  The owner was super loud and spent his time talking to his staff and running around …

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: After being there three times, decided to not give it a chance anymore. Perhaps the meat dishes are good, but the vegetarian ones are mediocre at best. Last time even found some meat in my vegetarian dish. Service is slow and not that friendly, owner seems not very nice to his staff.

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: Great value for money. Everything was delicious. They had English and Dutch menus which was very useful. Portions were really good. Vegetarian and meat dishes were all amazing.

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: This place was pathetic. It's a small restaurant. I had booked a table beforehand for a large group. They did not tell us that they don't accept card. So we had to go looking for an ATM. Food was just average with lot of spice. But the …

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: Beautiful stewed lamb. There was apparently a special bird that they flew in from Indonesia but didn't get to try it this time. Even the starter sticky rice roll is flavourful and well prepared. Sweet big mama behind the kitchen who's very warm and friendly.

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: We had an amazing Indonesian dinner. We had rendang ayam (chicken) and rendang tahu (tofu). It was really good, which brought us back to our trip through Indonesia. We will definitely go back to Belawi restaurant a few times

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: Good quality and authentica Indonesian food but when take away it is re-heated in the microwave instead of freshly made. It is still pretty good but can be fresher in that sense. Would still recommend it!

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: Very nice eating place. The only problem was that they asked us if we'd like a dish spicy or mild, but even after we asked for mild, the dish was very hot, even by our Indian standards. Very friendly staff.

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: Great food, nice and welcoming staff. (Cash only).

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: Our other favourite Indo place, especially if we want a takeaway. A bit of a ride by tram or bike, but the classic dishes are as good as ever. Keep it up!

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: Offered Indonesian specialties. Great quality of food. They also provide Thai cuisine.you have to prepare cash since they do not have any pin machine

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: This is the most "Gezellige" family-run indonesian restaurant in West. They dont accept card so bring cash. Feel at home and enjoy their hospitality and awsome recepies. They also do catering. Try nasi rames and yoi have to order their sate with pork. Its great

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi

Let's only regulars, Dutch or people that have spent a bit more money on food pay by pin. Food was great though.

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: A classic of Indonesian food in Amsterdam. Great attention. Good prices. In summer they have a terrace.i recommend to make reservations. Also works as take away.

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: I have been here already 20 times and it never disappoints me. Such an amazing restaurant with great food, fun easy going service and very reasonable prices. My favorite restaurant of Amsterdam.

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi

Review Text: Fantastic, delicious, and huge dishes. Service was OK. Great value for money. The vibe was warm and friendly. The only drawback was that the don’t accept any cards as payment.

Name: Indonesisch restaurant Betawi
Review Text: Simply superb. Traditional flavors, great value and lovely service. My new favorite restaurant in town and will absolutely come back again!
